content: Received in good condition in three weeks.  The charger and the cable were packed in two smaller boxes with the main box.  The size is quite small compared to what is shown in the description. See the attached pictures for comparison with my palm. However, the build is heavy and solid.  The LCD is of very poor quality with anything being barely visible right in front, and times out in a minute without anything connected. Also, while we can see the bottom portion, the upper portion of the display is cut off because the panel is improperly placed within the enclosure. A clear manufacturing defect.  The button on the right cycles between showing the status of each of the eight ports.  There are four rubber feet at the bottom for grip.  The supplied power cable is merely 1m in length. Not sure how much money they save by cutting such corners, but at the price, should've definitely been at least 2m.  At US $16.99, after various seller discounts, this was a decent deal.

content: Received in good condition in three weeks.  The charger and the cable were packed in two smaller boxes with the main box. The LCD is of very poor quality with anything being barely visible right in front, and times out in a minute without anything connected. Also, while we can see the bottom portion, the upper portion of the display is cut off because the panel is improperly placed within the enclosure. A clear manufacturing defect.  The button on the right cycles between showing the status of each of the eight ports.  There are four rubber feet at the bottom for grip.  The supplied power cable is merely 1m in length. Not sure how much money they save by cutting such corners, but at the price, should've definitely been at least 2m.  At US $16.99, after various seller discounts, this was a decent deal.

author: Timmy Zboncak
content: Works on linux & win 10[dont own a mac os];works also as otg[microusb].read/write speeds past 27MB/s must generate much heat[sata&nvme] hence the need for m.2 COPPER heatsink.The aluminium body only grab 5-10% of heat accumulated on ssd surface[works by 'radiation'].What we need,for instant & efficient heat dissipation, is heat dissipation by contact:of m.2 heatsink with ssd with thermalpad in between:to prolong ssd lifespan & protect valuable data, bcos we need to instantly draw heat away from ssd,NOT from the aluminium body.M.2 heatsink:thickness for one ontop ssd,0.8mm-2.0mm;one underneath ssd,0.8mm-1.0mm.Putting heatsink ontop&under ssd is much faster direct heat dissipation method,so put heatsink first! Recommend store & product.

author: Tomas Strosin
content: So glad & fortunate it arrived safely.All metallic m.2 casings only do 10% of heat dissipation. M.2 ssd accumulates heat on surface,radiates only a fraction of it to aluminium casing:bad for the ssd;therefore you MUST apply 'direct' ssd [copper] heatsink [thermalpad in middle] to ssd surface to quicky remove that heat and very much PREVENT its accumulation. Never put your m.2 ssd into any enclosure without first APPLYING HEATSINK [M.2] on it:amongst other things, for longer lifespan & your data safety! Fitting M.2 copper heatsink specs [ontop ssd surface] =thickness,0.8mm - 2.0mm. Waiting to get anoda m.2 copper heatsink batch [1.0mm and/or 0.8mm]to apply underneath the ssd.

author: Drew Ryan
content: It seems to be a good graphics card. Arrived to the US on-time. The HDMI display worked out of the box. I've updated it with the latest AMD Drivers for an RX 580, and there have been no problems thus far after doing so. In a build with a Ryzen 5 5500, without changing any settings, I average 60 FPS in Guilty Gear Strive with only a 9 degree change in temperature. However, I think an RX 580 should be performing better than this. An oddity is how when I boot my PC, you see a fuzzy graphic that you'd normally see when a GPU is dead, but it goes away in just seconds and it operates normally afterwards. I suppose it's no immediate concern, but I will be replacing the thermal paste with high grade Noctua just to be safe. It's about what I expected buying an $80 USD graphics card, but it will service for now until I can afford a good replacement. I will update my review with screenshots when possible.

author: Craig Bernhard
content: It is shorter than declared. 5 meters is exact dimension for one door (190cm+190cm+70 cm). However, shipped item is shorter than declared (instead 2x5m it is 4x240cm). This mean that with declared 10 meters (in reality 960-970 cm) you can apply it on only one door without extensions, with huge amount of waste.   It is very inconvenient for use. At least one side need to be extended, and it is not possible to make it in esthetically pleasing way.  If I knew that it is 4x2,5 and not 2x5m, I would not buy it (or would order more).   On the other side strap itself is good enough, and nicely adhesive.  If you plan to order it, plan for an extra length which will be needed. 70 meters, which is really about 69m, will be good for 12 doors, and you will have about 12m of waste (28 pieces, all bit shorter than 45cm).  It would be much better to have it as on 10m long strip, or 2x5m or even 5x2m, as it will produce much less waste.

author: Dexter Will
content: Delivered in 15 days, great. Bought 1 meter for testing. The cover was too difficult to pull off. The uncovered side wasn't very sticky, and after washing lost quite a bit of strength, even after hanging it to dry overnight. It's not very useful for sticking horizontal objects such as a carpet, for the simple reason that there's dust everywhere, unless you're in a clean room, and it won't steak with least bit of dust around, also due to direction of the force applied. For wall hanging (or other straight surface), it seems to work well (given ~30cm of the stuff) with a flat object like a postcard, but I tried to hang a small plastic usb splitter and it fell off after a day. Cool gimmick, but moreso for children or pranksters than serious business. PROTIP: Keep the cover for reusing, or better yet a non transparent cover from another tape (eg velcro) - no fingerprints and easier to press each side.
